Name: Observation_Information
Description: The Observation_Information class provides information about a science observation.

Name: release_number
Description: Release_number is the number of a scheduled release of InSight data from PDS. The first Insight data release is Release 1. The release_number for a given product is always the first release in which it appears, and does not change if the product is revised later.

Name: mission_phase_name
Description: The mission_phase_name identifies a time period within the mission.

Name: ATLO
Description: The ATLO mission phase (Assembly, Test, and Launch Operations) is the time of spacecraft and instrument assembly and test. During this phase data products are generated using flight hardware. They are usually not part of the final PDS archive but may be used for testing and peer review.

Name: CRUISE
Description: The cruise mission phase is from the time of escape from Earth's orbit through the time of entry into Mars' orbit. Some data products may be generated during this time, including instrument checkout data.

Name: DEVELOPMENT
Description: The development mission phase refers to the period of data processing software development and testing, before instruments are integrated with the spacecraft. Data products generated during this phase are usually not part of the final PDS archive but may be used for testing and peer review.

Name: SURFACE MISSION
Description: The surface mission phase is the time from arrival at Mars through the end of surface operations, including the primary mission and any extended missions that may take place.

Name: TEST
Description: The test mission phase is not a time period but a placeholder for the mission_phase_name value, used for data products generating during all project tests such as ORTs, SVTs and thread tests. Data products generated in this way are usually not part of the final PDS archive but may be used for testing and peer review.

Name: product_type
Description: The product_type identifies a group of data products within a collection that have some property in common, such as processing level, resolution, or instrument-specific setting.

Name: spacecraft_clock_start_count
Description: The spacecraft_clock_start_count is the value of the spacecraft clock at the beginning of an observation.

Name: spacecraft_clock_stop_count
Description: The spacecraft_clock_stop_count is the value of the spacecraft clock at the end of an observation.

Name: spacecraft_clock_count_partition
Description: The spacecraft_clock_count_partition provides the clock partition active for the spacecraft_clock_start_count and spacecraft_clock_stop_count attributes.

Name: sol_number
Description: Sol_number is the number of the Mars day on which an observation was acquired. Landing day is Sol 0.

Name: start_sol_number
Description: Start_sol_number is the number of the Mars day on which a multiple-day observation was begun. Landing day is Sol 0.

Name: stop_sol_number
Description: Stop_sol_number is the number of the Mars day on which a multiple-day observation was ended. Landing day is Sol 0.

Name: start_local_mean_solar_time
Description: Start_local_mean_solar_time is the local mean solar time, as defined in the main PDS4 data dictionary, at the beginning of an observation.

Name: stop_local_mean_solar_time
Description: Stop_local_mean_solar_time is the local mean solar time, as defined in the main PDS4 data dictionary, at the end of an observation.

Name: start_local_true_solar_time
Description: Start_local_true_solar_time is the local true solar time, as defined in the main PDS4 data dictionary, at the beginning of an observation.

Name: stop_local_true_solar_time
Description: Stop_local_true_solar_time is the local true solar time, as defined in the main PDS4 data dictionary, at the end of an observation.

Name: local_mean_solar_time_sol
Description: The local_mean_solar_time_sol element specifies the number of solar days elapsed since a reference day (e.g. the day on which a landing vehicle set down) for local mean solar time (LMST). Days are measured in rotations of the planet in question from midnight to midnight. The reference day is '0', as Landing day is Sol 0. If before Landing day, then value will be less than or equal to '0'and can be negative.

Name: local_true_solar_time_sol
Description: The local_true_solar_time_sol element specifies the number of solar days elapsed since a reference day (e.g. the day on which a landing vehicle set down) for local true solar time (LTST). Days are measured in rotations of the planet in question from midnight to midnight. The reference day is '0', as Landing day is Sol 0. If before Landing day, then value will be less than or equal to '0'and can be negative.

Name: start_solar_longitude
Description: Start_solar_longitude is the solar longitude, as defined in the main PDS4 data dictionary, at the beginning of an observation.

Name: stop_solar_longitude
Description: Stop_solar_longitude is the solar longitude, as defined in the main PDS4 data dictionary, at the end of an observation.

Name: observation_id
Description: The observation_id uniquely identifies an Insight science observation.

Name: sequence_id
Description: The sequence_id identifies the Insight planning sequence associated with a science product.

Name: sequence_version_id
Description: The sequence_version_id identifies the version of an Insight planning sequence associated with a science product.

Name: software_name
Description: Software_name identifies the processing software used to generate a data product.

Name: software_version_id
Description: Software_version_id identifies the version of the processing software used to generate a data product.

Name: SEIS_Instrument_Parameters
Description: Attributes specific to the InSight Seismometer data products

Name: channel_name
Description: The SEED data products for the SEIS instrument contain data from a single instrument channel. The channel_name identifies which SEIS channel data are included in the SEED file.

Name: SP_1
Description: The SP 1 channel records data from the first axis of the SP seismometer.

Name: SP_2
Description: The SP 2 channel records data from the first axis of the SP seismometer.

Name: SP_3
Description: The SP 3 channel records data from the first axis of the SP seismometer.

Name: VBB_1_Position
Description: The VBB 1 position channel records position data from the first axis of the VBB seismometer.

Name: VBB_1_Temperature
Description: The VBB 1 temperature channel records temperature data from the first axis of the VBB seismometer.

Name: VBB_1_Velocity
Description: The VBB 1 velocity channel records velocity data from the first axis of the VBB seismometer.

Name: VBB_2_Position
Description: The VBB 2 position channel records position data from the second axis of the VBB seismometer.

Name: VBB_2_Temperature
Description: The VBB 2 temperature channel records temperature data from the second axis of the VBB seismometer.

Name: VBB_2_Velocity
Description: The VBB 2 velocity channel records velocity data from the second axis of the VBB seismometer.

Name: VBB_3_Position
Description: The VBB 3 position channel records position data from the third axis of the VBB seismometer.

Name: VBB_3_Temperature
Description: The VBB 3 temperature channel records temperature data from the third axis of the VBB seismometer.

Name: VBB_3_Velocity
Description: The VBB 3 velocity channel records velocity data from the third axis of the VBB seismometer.

Name: measurement_type
Description: Measurement_type indicates the seismometer (VBB or SP) and whether the data were collected in continuous or event mode used in a measurement.

Name: SP_Event
Description: Event mode data from the SP seismometer.

Name: VBB_Continuous
Description: Continuous mode data from the VBB seismometer.

Name: VBB_Event
Description: Event mode data from the VBB seismometer.

Name: sampling_rate
Description: Sampling_rate specifics the rate (samples/time) that data from an instrument were sampled and recorded.

Name: measurement_duration
Description: Measurement_duration indicates the length of time covered by a given measurement.

Name: instrument_clock_start_count
Description: The instrument_clock_start_count is the value of the instrument clock at the beginning of an observation.
